        <heading>Property Tax Assessment</heading>
        <section eId="sec_12_65c">
          <num>12-65c</num>
          <heading>Deferral of increased assessments due to rehabilitation: Definitions</heading>
          <subsection eId="12_65c__subsec_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content>
              <p>“Rehabilitation area” means any municipality, or a part thereof, that contains one or more properties that are deteriorated, deteriorating, substandard or detrimental to the safety, health, welfare or general economic well-being of the community;</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="12_65c__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content>
              <p>“Rehabilitation” means the improvement or repair of a structure or facilities appurtenant thereto, exclusive of general maintenance or minor repairs.
(Return to ChapterTable of Contents)(Return toList of Chapters)(Return toList of Titles)</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
